Rodney Jones (born July 28, 1968 in Lafayette, Louisiana) is a professional boxer in the Light Middleweight division.[1] He's a Former NABF and WBO NABO Light Middleweight champion.[2] Early in his career when Rodney was 28 years old, he beat an eighteen year old Antonio Margarito by a ten round decision. The young Mexican, went on to become a three-time World Champion.[3] In he's first effort at a World Championship he would lose to Harry Simon.[4] On February 3, 2007 Jones lost to world champion Cory Spinks in Silver Spurs Arena, Kissimmee, Florida.[5]
